-- Roper Industries to buy healthcare services company for $1 billion
-- 
-- Wed Apr 17, 2013 4:42pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/17/us-roperindustries-acquisition-idUSBRE93G14J20130417

 

 (Reuters) - Diversified U.S. manufacturer Roper Industries Inc said it would buy healthcare services company Managed Health Care Associates Inc for $1 billion in an all-cash deal to expand its presence in the healthcare market. 
 Roper said the deal, expected to be completed within 30 days, would add $95 million in earnings before income tax depreciation and amortization in the first year after the acquisition. (Reporting by Tej Sapru in Bangalore)